title: Spring Talks Roundup
---

I've recently been lucky enough to travel to some fascinating places and arrange events, give invited talks, and participate in panel discussions. Some details and pictures are gathered below: a heartfelt thanks to _all_ of the organisers who have made this possible!

April 2026 has already involved events at [Robosoft 2026](https://www.robosoft2026.org/), Kanazawa, and Tokyo, where I:

- Gave an invited talk and joined a panel discussion on Monolithic Soft Systems in Robotics.
- Gave an invited talk on non-contact object manipulation in a workshop "_Exploiting Fluids and Embodied Intelligence in Soft Robotics._"
- Helped to organise a new workshop: "_Electrical Impedance Tomography-Based Tactile Sensing: Bridging Soft Robotics and Artificial Touch_", where I also joined the closing panel discussion.

Additionally, at the end of February I visited the [Max Planck Institute for Intelligent Systems](https://is.mpg.de/en) in Stuttgart, to speak in their 2026 Scientific Symposium.

Next month I'll be at [ICRA 2026](https://2026.ieee-icra.org/) in Vienna as one of the workshop organisers bringing together the community in large-area tactile sensing. Find out more [here](https://large-area-tactile-sensing.github.io/).

